	<section id="presentation_text" align="LEFT" spacing="0x10" autospace="true" columns="0" expanded="true">
		<text id="introduction" x="25" y="50" width="722" height="" autosize="H" style="INTRO" visible="true" fx="INTRO_SHOW" hidefx="INTRO_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Social learning theory focuses on the learning that occurs within a social context. It shows that people learn from one another. Albert Bandura, one of the pioneer researchers and leading proponents of this theory, determined that four conditions are necessary to successfully model behavior.</content>
