			<transcript translate="true">While some researchers explore the internal workings of imitation, others look at the practical application of imitating others. Social learning theory focuses on the learning that occurs within a social context. It shows that people learn from one another. Albert Bandura, one of the pioneer researchers and leading proponents of this theory, determined that four conditions are necessary to successfully model behavior. Click each condition to learn more.</transcript>
